AI ANIMATION EDITOR MVP (Your Project Summary)

Goal: A web-based animation editor where the user uploads one full-body image, poses the character using MediaPipe joints, applies warp-based animation, uses a CapCut-style timeline, adds camera motions, previews in real time, and exports a 1080p MP4 at 30 fps all running frontend-first on Windows without GPU-heavy models.

1. Core Platform

  • React + Vite + TailwindCSS

  • Konva.js for the 19201080 canvas rendering

  • Dark mode UI, purple accents

  • Workspace background: solid black

  • Runs entirely frontend-first, Python backend comes later

  • No ControlNet / heavy diffusion due to MX230 GPU constraints

2. Input

  • Upload one single full-body image (PNG/JPG)

  • Display it centered on 19201080 canvas

  • Show bounding box + scaling handles

3. Segmentation (SAM2 - High Quality)

  • Call SAM2 (local or server) to extract:

    • Foreground character mask

    • Background layer

  • Maintain:

    • originalImage

    • foregroundMask

    • foregroundImageCutout

    • backgroundLayer (solid black for MVP, continuous)

4. Pose Detection (MediaPipe)

  • Use MediaPipe Pose with:

    • 33 keypoints

    • Skeleton lines

    • Confidence thresholding

  • Provide:

    • Draggable joints (Konva circles)

    • Line segments connecting joints

    • Sliders for rotation of limbs (optional MVP)

  • State:

    js
    pose = {
  keypoints: [{x, y, visible}, ...],
  connections: [...]
}

5. Animation System (Tween Interpolation 30fps)

  • Keyframe-based animation:

    • Frame rate locked at 30 FPS

    • Linear interpolation between pose keyframes

  • Timeline stores:

    js
    animations: [
  {
    id,
    type: "pose",
    start: timeInSec,
    end: timeInSec,
    keyframes: {
      startPose,
      endPose
    }
  }
]

  • Preview engine

    • Runs at 30fps

    • Computes tweened pose

    • Warps image using AV2-style mesh warp

6. Warp Engine (Actual Visual Animation)

  • Warp original foreground image based on:

    • Pose joint deltas

    • Mesh deformation grid

    • Bilinear interpolation on mesh

  • Pipeline:

    1. Convert joints mesh

    2. Apply deltas to mesh

    3. Re-render warped image to canvas

No re-generating pixels; you are warping the original image.

7. Camera System (Cinematic Effects)

Effects you support:

Zoom

Canvas scale changes (Konva stage scale)

Pan

Offset X/Y translation

Rotate

Stage rotation

Blur

CSS blur or canvas filter applied on top layer

Stored as:

js
cameraKeyframes: [
  { time, zoom, panX, panY, rotation, blur }
]

Interpolated every frame during playback.

8. CapCut-Style Timeline

Your UI timeline includes:

Layers:

  • Pose (keyframes)

  • Warp (auto)

  • Camera (zoom/pan/rotate/blur)

  • Background (static)

  • Audio (future but not now)

Features:

  • Drag blocks

  • Resize blocks

  • Scrub playhead

  • Add keyframe at current time

  • Delete keyframe

  • Preview updates immediately

9. Playback

  • Real-time preview at 30 FPS

  • Canvas updates pose warp camera composite

  • Loop button

  • Play / pause

10. Export MP4 (Frontend)

Using ffmpeg-wasm:

Process:

  1. Render each frame to offscreen canvas (19201080)

  2. Capture PNG or RGBA bytes per frame

  3. Pass frames to ffmpeg

  4. Output H.264 MP4, 30fps

  5. Download file

Constraints:

  • Needs batching to avoid memory overflow

  • Use -preset ultrafast

    """

mp_segmentation.py FULL WORKING CODE

python
import cv2
import numpy as np
import base64
from io import BytesIO
from PIL import Image
from fastapi import UploadFile

import mediapipe as mp


async def run_segmentation(file: UploadFile):
    """
    Full segmentation pipeline:
      1. Load image from UploadFile
      2. Run MediaPipe Selfie Segmentation (model_selection=1)
      3. Convert float mask  uint8 mask
      4. Compute tight bounding box using cv2.boundingRect
      5. Create transparent PNG cutout of person
      6. Return base64 PNGs + bbox + original dimensions
    """

    # =======================
    # Read uploaded image
    # =======================
    contents = await file.read()
    npimg = np.frombuffer(contents, np.uint8)
    image = cv2.imdecode(npimg, cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED)

    if image is None:
        raise ValueError("Invalid image file")

    height, width = image.shape[:2]

    # =======================
    # Load MediaPipe model
    # =======================
    mp_selfie = mp.solutions.selfie_segmentation.SelfieSegmentation(model_selection=1)

    # Convert to RGB for MediaPipe
    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

    # Run segmentation
    result = mp_selfie.process(image_rgb)
    mask_float = result.segmentation_mask

    if mask_float is None:
        raise ValueError("Segmentation mask unavailable")

    # =======================
    # Convert mask to uint8
    # =======================
    # mask_float: values 01
    # convert to 0 or 255
    mask_uint8 = (mask_float > 0.5).astype(np.uint8) * 255

    # =======================
    # Compute bounding box
    # =======================
    x, y, w, h = cv2.boundingRect(mask_uint8)

    # =======================
    # Create transparent foreground PNG
    # =======================
    # Convert BGR  RGBA
    rgba = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGBA)

    # Apply mask (transparent where mask=0)
    rgba[:, :, 3] = mask_uint8

    # =======================
    # Encode mask PNG
    # =======================
    _, mask_png = cv2.imencode(".png", mask_uint8)
    mask_b64 = base64.b64encode(mask_png.tobytes()).decode("utf-8")

    # =======================
    # Encode foreground cutout PNG
    # =======================
    pil_img = Image.fromarray(rgba)
    buf = BytesIO()
    pil_img.save(buf, format="PNG")
    foreground_b64 = base64.b64encode(buf.getvalue()).decode("utf-8")

    # =======================
    # Final response JSON
    # =======================
    return {
        "mask": mask_b64,
        "foreground": foreground_b64,
        "bbox": [int(x), int(y), int(w), int(h)],
        "width": int(width),
        "height": int(height)
    }

2.3 Full poseDetector.js Implementation

This matches your exact spec:

  • Load the MediaPipe Tasks model from CDN

  • Initialize VisionTaskRunner

  • Run detection in client-side JS

  • Return the 33-keypoint array

  • Convert normalized coordinates:

    ini
    x = kp.x * 1920
y = kp.y * 1080

  • Base pose is cloned once

  • Use all joints (per your choice C2)

src/utils/poseDetector.js

js
import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest/wasm"
  );

  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath:
        "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest/models/pose_landmarker.task"
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE"
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  const rawJoints = result.landmarks[0];

  // Convert normalized  canvas coords
  const joints = rawJoints.map((kp) => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080
  }));

  return joints;
}

import { useEditor } from "../context/EditorContext";
import { detectPose, loadPoseModel } from "../utils/poseDetector";

export default function TopToolbar({ showToast }) {
  const {
    image,
    foreground,
    joints,
    setJoints,
    setBasePose
  } = useEditor();

  // Detect Pose button action
  async function handleDetectPose() {
    if (!foreground) {
      showToast("Run segmentation first.");
      return;
    }
    if (!image) {
      showToast("Upload an image first.");
      return;
    }

    try {
      await loadPoseModel();

      // Create a bitmap for MediaPipe detector
      const img = await createImageBitmap(image);

      const detected = await detectPose(img);

      // Save joints
      setJoints(detected);
      setBasePose(JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(detected))); // deep clone

    } catch (err) {
      showToast("Pose detection failed.");
      console.error(err);
    }
  }

  return (
    <div className="w-full h-12 bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-700 flex items-center gap-4 px-4">

      <label className="cursor-pointer">
        <input
          type="file"
          className="hidden"
          onChange={(e) => {
            const file = e.target.files?.[0];
            if (!file) return;

            const url = URL.createObjectURL(file);
            const img = new Image();
            img.onload = () => {
              // frontend stores original HTMLImageElement
              const canvas = document.createElement("canvas");
              canvas.width = img.width;
              canvas.height = img.height;
              const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");
              ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0);
              const bmp = canvas;

              const arr = new Image();
              arr.src = url;

              const { setImage } = useEditor.getState
                ? useEditor()
                : { setImage: () => {} };

              useEditor().setImage(arr);
            };
            img.src = url;
          }}
        />
        <span className="text-brandPurple">Upload Image</span>
      </label>

      <button
        onClick={handleDetectPose}
        className="px-3 py-1 bg-brandPurple rounded"
      >
        Detect Pose
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

jsx
import { Stage, Layer, Rect, Image as KonvaImage, Circle, Line, Group } from "react-konva";
import { useEditor } from "../context/EditorContext";
import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";
import { tweenValue } from "../utils/tween";
import { warpImage } from "../utils/warpEngine";

// MediaPipe Pose connections
// Official MP pose connections (pairs of index numbers)
const POSE_CONNECTIONS = [
  [11, 13], [13, 15], // Left arm
  [12, 14], [14, 16], // Right arm
  [11, 12],           // Shoulders
  [12, 24], [11, 23], // Torso sides
  [23, 24],           // Hips
  [23, 25], [25, 27], // Left leg
  [27, 29], [29, 31], // Left shin/foot
  [24, 26], [26, 28], // Right leg
  [28, 30], [30, 32], // Right shin/foot
];

// Joint drawing radius
const JOINT_RADIUS = 6;
const HIT_RADIUS = 16; // Larger for easier dragging

export default function CanvasStage({ showToast }) {
  const {
    image,
    foreground,
    joints,
    setJoints,
    basePose,
    imageOffset,
    setImageOffset,
    camera,
    isPlaying,
    keyframes,
    currentFrame
  } = useEditor();

  const stageRef = useRef(null);
  const [scale, setScale] = useState(1);

  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  // 1) AUTO SCALE TO FIT SCREEN (downscale only, preserve aspect)
  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  useEffect(() => {
    function updateScale() {
      const containerW = window.innerWidth - 260; // right panel width
      const containerH = window.innerHeight - 180; // timeline + toolbar

      const scaleX = containerW / 1920;
      const scaleY = containerH / 1080;
      const newScale = Math.min(scaleX, scaleY, 1);

      setScale(newScale);
    }

    updateScale();
    window.addEventListener("resize", updateScale);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("resize", updateScale);
  }, []);

  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  // 2) AUTO-CENTER PERSON AFTER SEGMENTATION
  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!foreground) return;

    // center the person
    const centerX = 1920 / 2;
    const centerY = 1080 / 2;

    setImageOffset({ x: centerX - 200, y: centerY - 400 });
  }, [foreground]);

  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  // 3) DRAGGING LOGIC
  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  const [draggingIndex, setDraggingIndex] = useState(null);

  function getPointerPos() {
    const stage = stageRef.current;
    if (!stage) return { x: 0, y: 0 };
    const pointer = stage.getPointerPosition() || { x: 0, y: 0 };

    return {
      x: pointer.x / scale,
      y: pointer.y / scale,
    };
  }

  function onMouseDown(e) {
    if (!joints.length || isPlaying) return;

    const pos = getPointerPos();

    // detect if clicking near any joint
    for (let i = 0; i < joints.length; i++) {
      const j = joints[i];
      const dx = pos.x - j.x;
      const dy = pos.y - j.y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

      if (dist <= HIT_RADIUS) {
        setDraggingIndex(i);
        return;
      }
    }
  }

  function onMouseMove(e) {
    if (draggingIndex === null) return;

    const pos = getPointerPos();
    const rootLeft = 23;
    const rootRight = 24;

    const updated = [...joints];

    // ROOT DRAGGING (move skeleton + imageOffset)
    if (draggingIndex === rootLeft || draggingIndex === rootRight) {
      const dx = pos.x - updated[draggingIndex].x;
      const dy = pos.y - updated[draggingIndex].y;

      // move all joints
      for (let i = 0; i < updated.length; i++) {
        updated[i] = {
          x: updated[i].x + dx,
          y: updated[i].y + dy,
        };
      }

      // move image with skeleton
      setImageOffset({
        x: imageOffset.x + dx,
        y: imageOffset.y + dy,
      });

      setJoints(updated);
      return;
    }

    // NON-ROOT DRAGGING: move only that joint
    updated[draggingIndex] = { x: pos.x, y: pos.y };
    setJoints(updated);
  }

  function onMouseUp() {
    setDraggingIndex(null);
  }

  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  // 4) CAMERA GROUP TRANSFORM
  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  const cameraGroupProps = {
    scaleX: camera.zoom,
    scaleY: camera.zoom,
    offsetX: 960,
    offsetY: 540,
    x: 960 + camera.panX,
    y: 540 + camera.panY,
    rotation: camera.rotate,
  };

  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  // 5) RENDER
  // -------------------------------------------------------------
  return (
    <div className="relative w-full h-full flex justify-center items-center">
      <Stage
        ref={stageRef}
        width={1920 * scale}
        height={1080 * scale}
        scaleX={scale}
        scaleY={scale}
        onMouseDown={onMouseDown}
        onMouseMove={onMouseMove}
        onMouseUp={onMouseUp}
      >
        <Layer>
          {/* CAMERA GROUP WRAPS EVERYTHING EXCEPT UI */}
          <Group {...cameraGroupProps}>

            {/* BLACK BACKGROUND */}
            <Rect x={0} y={0} width={1920} height={1080} fill="black" />

            {/* PERSON FOREGROUND IMAGE */}
            {foreground && (
              <KonvaImage
                image={foreground}
                x={imageOffset.x}
                y={imageOffset.y}
              />
            )}

            {/* BONES */}
            {joints.length > 0 &&
              POSE_CONNECTIONS.map(([a, b], i) => {
                if (!joints[a] || !joints[b]) return null;
                return (
                  <Line
                    key={i}
                    points={[joints[a].x, joints[a].y, joints[b].x, joints[b].y]}
                    stroke="#00FFFF"
                    strokeWidth={3}
                  />
                );
              })
            }

            {/* JOINTS */}
            {joints.length > 0 &&
              joints.map((j, i) => (
                <Circle
                  key={i}
                  x={j.x}
                  y={j.y}
                  radius={JOINT_RADIUS}
                  fill="#FF0000"
                />
              ))
            }

          </Group>
        </Layer>
      </Stage>
    </div>
  );
}

export async function segmentImage(file) {
  const formData = new FormData();
  formData.append("file", file);

  let res;
  try {
    res = await fetch("http://127.0.0.1:8000/segment", {
      method: "POST",
      body: formData,
    });
  } catch (err) {
    throw new Error("BACKEND_OFFLINE");
  }

  if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Segmentation error");

  const json = await res.json();

  if (json.error) {
    throw new Error(json.error);
  }

  return json;
}

export function base64ToImage(b64) {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    const img = new Image();
    img.onload = () => resolve(img);
    img.src = "data:image/png;base64," + b64;
  });
}

import { useEditor } from "../context/EditorContext";
import { segmentImage } from "../utils/api";
import { detectPose, loadPoseModel } from "../utils/poseDetector";
import { base64ToImage } from "../utils/base64ToImage";

export default function TopToolbar({ showToast }) {
  const {
    setImage,
    setForeground,
    setMask,
    setBbox,
    setJoints,
    setBasePose,
    joints,
    foreground,
  } = useEditor();

  // =========================================================
  // 1) UPLOAD IMAGE
  // =========================================================
  async function handleUpload(e) {
    const file = e.target.files?.[0];
    if (!file) return;

    const img = new Image();
    img.onload = () => {
      setImage(img);
      // reset pose + segmentation
      setForeground(null);
      setMask(null);
      setBbox(null);
      setJoints([]);
      setBasePose(null);
    };
    img.src = URL.createObjectURL(file);

    // store file so segmentation can use it
    e.target.value = "";
    window._uploadedFile = file;
  }

  // =========================================================
  // 2) SEGMENT PERSON (BACKEND CALL)
  // =========================================================
  async function handleSegment() {
    const file = window._uploadedFile;
    if (!file) {
      showToast("Upload an image first.");
      return;
    }

    try {
      const result = await segmentImage(file);

      // decode base64 images
      const fg = await base64ToImage(result.foreground);
      const maskImg = await base64ToImage(result.mask);

      setForeground(fg);
      setMask(maskImg);
      setBbox(result.bbox);

      // clear pose until pose detection is run
      setJoints([]);
      setBasePose(null);

    } catch (err) {
      if (err.message === "BACKEND_OFFLINE") {
        showToast("Segmentation backend not running.");
      } else {
        showToast("Segmentation failed.");
      }
      console.error(err);
    }
  }

  // =========================================================
  // 3) DETECT POSE (MediaPipe)
  // =========================================================
  async function handleDetectPose() {
    if (!foreground) {
      showToast("Run segmentation first.");
      return;
    }

    try {
      await loadPoseModel();

      // Create imageBitmap for detector
      const bitmap = await createImageBitmap(foreground);

      const detected = await detectPose(bitmap);

      setJoints(detected);
      setBasePose(JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(detected))); // deep clone

    } catch (err) {
      showToast("Pose detection failed.");
      console.error(err);
    }
  }

  // =========================================================
  // 4) ADD FRAME (only allowed if pose exists)
  // =========================================================
  const addFrame = () => {
    if (!joints.length) {
      showToast("Detect pose first.");
      return;
    }

    const {
      keyframes,
      setKeyframes,
      imageOffset,
      camera,
    } = useEditor();

    const frame = {
      id: Date.now(),
      joints: JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(joints)),
      offset: { ...imageOffset },
      camera: { ...camera },
      timeMs: keyframes.length * 800, // 800ms per frame
    };

    setKeyframes([...keyframes, frame]);
  };

  // =========================================================
  // RENDER
  // =========================================================
  return (
    <div className="w-full h-12 bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-700 flex items-center gap-6 px-4">

      {/* Upload */}
      <label className="cursor-pointer text-brandPurple">
        <input type="file" className="hidden" onChange={handleUpload} />
        Upload Image
      </label>

      {/* Segment */}
      <button
        onClick={handleSegment}
        className="px-3 py-1 bg-brandPurple rounded"
      >
        Segment Person
      </button>

      {/* Detect Pose */}
      <button
        onClick={handleDetectPose}
        className="px-3 py-1 bg-brandPurple rounded"
      >
        Detect Pose
      </button>

      {/* Add Frame */}
      <button
        onClick={addFrame}
        className="px-3 py-1 bg-brandPurple rounded"
      >
        Add Frame
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

import { createContext, useContext, useState } from "react";

const EditorContext = createContext(null);
export const useEditor = () => useContext(EditorContext);

export function EditorProvider({ children }) {
  const [image, setImage] = useState(null);
  const [foreground, setForeground] = useState(null);
  const [mask, setMask] = useState(null);
  const [bbox, setBbox] = useState(null);

  const [imageOffset, setImageOffset] = useState({ x: 0, y: 0 });

    zoom: 1,
    panX: 0,
    panY: 0,
    rotate: 0
  });

  const [keyframes, setKeyframes] = useState([]);
  const [currentFrame, setCurrentFrame] = useState(0);
  const [isPlaying, setIsPlaying] = useState(false);

  // interpolated values during playback (CanvasStage reads these)
  const [interpolatedJoints, setInterpolatedJoints] = useState([]);
  const [interpolatedOffset, setInterpolatedOffset] = useState({ x: 0, y: 0 });
  const [interpolatedCamera, setInterpolatedCamera] = useState({

    panX: 0,
    panY: 0,

  return (

2. Update App.jsx Add the complete playback loop

Replace your App.jsx with this final version:

jsx
import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from "react";
import { EditorProvider, useEditor } from "./context/EditorContext";

import CanvasStage from "./components/CanvasStage";
import Timeline from "./components/Timeline";
import TopToolbar from "./components/TopToolbar";
import RightPanel from "./components/RightPanel";
import PlayButton from "./components/PlayButton";
import Toast from "./components/Toast";

import { lerp } from "./utils/tween";

function AppInner() {
  const {
    keyframes,
    isPlaying,
    setIsPlaying,
    setCurrentFrame,

    setInterpolatedJoints,
    setInterpolatedOffset,
    setInterpolatedCamera,
  } = useEditor();

  const [toast, setToast] = useState(null);

  const requestRef = useRef(null);
  const playbackStartRef = useRef(null);

  // ===============================
  // PLAY LOOP (requestAnimationFrame)
  // ===============================
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!isPlaying || keyframes.length < 2) return;

    playbackStartRef.current = performance.now();

    const FRAME_DURATION = 800; // ms per frame
    const TOTAL_FRAMES = keyframes.length;

    const animate = (timestamp) => {
      const elapsed = timestamp - playbackStartRef.current;
      const totalAnimationDuration = FRAME_DURATION * TOTAL_FRAMES;

      let t = (elapsed % totalAnimationDuration) / FRAME_DURATION;

      let frameIndex = Math.floor(t);
      let localT = t - frameIndex;

      const nextIndex = (frameIndex + 1) % TOTAL_FRAMES;

      const A = keyframes[frameIndex];
      const B = keyframes[nextIndex];

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE JOINTS ----------------
      const jA = A.joints;
      const jB = B.joints;

      if (jA && jA.length && jB && jB.length) {
        const blended = jA.map((aj, i) => ({
          x: lerp(aj.x, jB[i].x, localT),
          y: lerp(aj.y, jB[i].y, localT),
        }));
        setInterpolatedJoints(blended);
      }

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE OFFSET ----------------
      setInterpolatedOffset({
        x: lerp(A.offset.x, B.offset.x, localT),
        y: lerp(A.offset.y, B.offset.y, localT),
      });

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE CAMERA ----------------
      setInterpolatedCamera({
        zoom: lerp(A.camera.zoom, B.camera.zoom, localT),
        panX: lerp(A.camera.panX, B.camera.panX, localT),
        panY: lerp(A.camera.panY, B.camera.panY, localT),
        rotate: lerp(A.camera.rotate, B.camera.rotate, localT),
      });

      setCurrentFrame(frameIndex);

      requestRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    };

    requestRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);

    return () => cancelAnimationFrame(requestRef.current);
  }, [isPlaying, keyframes]);

  return (
    <div className="w-screen h-screen flex flex-col overflow-hidden bg-black">
      <TopToolbar showToast={setToast} />
      <div className="flex flex-1">
        <div className="flex-1 flex justify-center items-center">
          <CanvasStage showToast={setToast} />

        <RightPanel />
      </div>
      <Timeline />
      <PlayButton showToast={setToast} />
      {toast && <Toast message={toast} onClose={() => setToast(null)} />}
    </div>
  );
}

import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";

// MediaPipe pose connections
const POSE_CONNECTIONS = [
  [11, 13], [13, 15], // Left arm
  [12, 14], [14, 16], // Right arm
  [11, 12],           // Shoulders
  [12, 24], [11, 23], // Torso sides
  [23, 24],           // Hips
  [23, 25], [25, 27], // Left leg
  [27, 29], [29, 31], // Left shin/foot
  [24, 26], [26, 28], // Right leg

];

const HIT_RADIUS = 16;

  const {
    image,
    joints,
    interpolatedJoints,
    imageOffset,
    interpolatedOffset,
    camera,
    interpolatedCamera,
    foreground,

    setImageOffset,
    isPlaying,
  } = useEditor();

  // Choose interpolated/live values depending on playback
  const activeJoints = isPlaying ? interpolatedJoints : joints;
  const activeOffset = isPlaying ? interpolatedOffset : imageOffset;
  const activeCamera = isPlaying ? interpolatedCamera : camera;

  const stageRef = useRef(null);
  const [scale, setScale] = useState(1);

  // ============================================
  // 1) AUTO SCALE DOWN, PRESERVE ASPECT RATIO
  // ============================================
  useEffect(() => {
    function updateScale() {
      const containerW = window.innerWidth - 260;   // right panel reserved
      const containerH = window.innerHeight - 180; // toolbar + timeline

      const scaleX = containerW / 1920;
      const scaleY = containerH / 1080;
      const newScale = Math.min(scaleX, scaleY, 1);

      setScale(newScale);
    }

    updateScale();
    window.addEventListener("resize", updateScale);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("resize", updateScale);
  }, []);

  // ============================================
  // 2) AUTO-CENTER PERSON AFTER SEGMENTATION
  // ============================================
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!foreground) return;

    const centerX = 1920 / 2;
    const centerY = 1080 / 2;

    setImageOffset({
      x: centerX - 200,
      y: centerY - 400,
    });
  }, [foreground]);

  // ============================================
  // 3) DRAGGING LOGIC
  // ============================================
  const [draggingIndex, setDraggingIndex] = useState(null);

    const stage = stageRef.current;
    if (!stage) return { x: 0, y: 0 };

    const pointer = stage.getPointerPosition() || { x: 0, y: 0 };
    return {
      x: pointer.x / scale,
      y: pointer.y / scale,
    };

    for (let i = 0; i < activeJoints.length; i++) {

      const dy = pos.y - j.y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

      if (dist <= HIT_RADIUS) {
        setDraggingIndex(i);
        return;
      }
    }
  }

  function onMouseMove() {
    if (draggingIndex === null) return;
    if (isPlaying) return;

    const pos = getPointerPos();
    const updated = [...activeJoints];

    const rootLeft = 23;
    const rootRight = 24;

      const dy = pos.y - updated[draggingIndex].y;

          y: updated[i].y + dy,

  }

  function onMouseUp() {
    setDraggingIndex(null);
  }

  // ============================================
  // 4) CAMERA GROUP TRANSFORM
  // ============================================
  const cameraGroupProps = {
    scaleX: activeCamera.zoom,
    scaleY: activeCamera.zoom,
    offsetX: 960,
    offsetY: 540,
    x: 960 + activeCamera.panX,
    y: 540 + activeCamera.panY,
    rotation: activeCamera.rotate,
  };

  // ============================================

        onMouseUp={onMouseUp}

                y={activeOffset.y}

            {activeJoints.length > 0 &&

                if (!activeJoints[a] || !activeJoints[b]) return null;

                return (

                    key={i}

                      activeJoints[a].x,
                      activeJoints[a].y,

                    stroke="#00FFFF"
                    strokeWidth={3}
                  />
                );
              })}

            {/* JOINTS */}
            {activeJoints.length > 0 &&

                <Circle
                  key={i}
                  x={j.x}
                  y={j.y}
                  radius={JOINT_RADIUS}
                  fill="#FF0000"
                />
              ))}

jsx
import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from "react";
import { EditorProvider, useEditor } from "./context/EditorContext";

import CanvasStage from "./components/CanvasStage";
import Timeline from "./components/Timeline";
import TopToolbar from "./components/TopToolbar";
import RightPanel from "./components/RightPanel";
import PlayButton from "./components/PlayButton";
import Toast from "./components/Toast";

import { lerp } from "./utils/tween";


// ==============================================
// INTERNAL APP (playback loop lives here)
// ==============================================
function AppInner() {
  const {
    keyframes,
    isPlaying,
    setIsPlaying,
    setCurrentFrame,

    setInterpolatedJoints,
    setInterpolatedOffset,
    setInterpolatedCamera,
  } = useEditor();

  const [toast, setToast] = useState(null);

  const requestRef = useRef(null);
  const playbackStartRef = useRef(null);

  // ==========================================
  // PLAY LOOP (requestAnimationFrame)
  // ==========================================
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!isPlaying || keyframes.length < 2) return;

    playbackStartRef.current = performance.now();

    const FRAME_DURATION = 800; // ms per frame
    const TOTAL_FRAMES = keyframes.length;

    const animate = (timestamp) => {
      const elapsed = timestamp - playbackStartRef.current;
      const totalAnimationDuration = FRAME_DURATION * TOTAL_FRAMES;

      // Global t for entire animation
      let t = (elapsed % totalAnimationDuration) / FRAME_DURATION;

      // Current frame index
      let frameIndex = Math.floor(t);
      let localT = t - frameIndex;

      // Next frame index (loop)
      const nextIndex = (frameIndex + 1) % TOTAL_FRAMES;

      const A = keyframes[frameIndex];
      const B = keyframes[nextIndex];

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE JOINTS ----------------
      const jA = A.joints;
      const jB = B.joints;

      if (jA && jA.length && jB && jB.length) {
        const blended = jA.map((aj, i) => ({
          x: lerp(aj.x, jB[i].x, localT),
          y: lerp(aj.y, jB[i].y, localT),
        }));
        setInterpolatedJoints(blended);
      }

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE OFFSET ----------------
      setInterpolatedOffset({
        x: lerp(A.offset.x, B.offset.x, localT),
        y: lerp(A.offset.y, B.offset.y, localT),
      });

      // ---------------- INTERPOLATE CAMERA ----------------
      setInterpolatedCamera({
        zoom: lerp(A.camera.zoom, B.camera.zoom, localT),
        panX: lerp(A.camera.panX, B.camera.panX, localT),
        panY: lerp(A.camera.panY, B.camera.panY, localT),
        rotate: lerp(A.camera.rotate, B.camera.rotate, localT),
      });

      // Update frame index so timeline highlights correctly
      setCurrentFrame(frameIndex);

      requestRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    };

    requestRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);

    // CLEANUP
    return () => cancelAnimationFrame(requestRef.current);

  }, [isPlaying, keyframes]);


  // ==========================================
  // RENDER
  // ==========================================
  return (
    <div className="w-screen h-screen flex flex-col overflow-hidden bg-black">

      <TopToolbar showToast={setToast} />

      <div className="flex flex-1">
        <div className="flex-1 flex justify-center items-center">
          <CanvasStage showToast={setToast} />
        </div>

        <RightPanel />
      </div>

      <Timeline />
      
      <PlayButton showToast={setToast} />

      {toast && <Toast message={toast} onClose={() => setToast(null)} />}
    </div>
  );
}


// ==============================================
// MAIN APP WRAPPER WITH CONTEXT PROVIDER
// ==============================================
export default function App() {
  return (
    <EditorProvider>
      <AppInner />
    </EditorProvider>
  );
}

js
export function lerp(a, b, t) {
  return a + (b - a) * t;
}

/**
 * Interpolates between two {x, y} points.
 */
export function lerpPoint(A, B, t) {
  return {
    x: lerp(A.x, B.x, t),
    y: lerp(A.y, B.y, t),
  };
}

/**
 * Interpolates an array of joints [{x,y}, ...] linearly.
 */
export function lerpJoints(jA, jB, t) {
  if (!jA || !jB || jA.length !== jB.length) return jA;
  return jA.map((p, i) => lerpPoint(p, jB[i], t));
}

export async function segmentImage(file) {
  const formData = new FormData();
  formData.append("file", file);

  let res;
  try {
    res = await fetch("http://127.0.0.1:8000/segment", {
      method: "POST",
      body: formData,
    });
  } catch (err) {
    throw new Error("BACKEND_OFFLINE");
  }

  if (!res.ok) {
    throw new Error("Segmentation failed");
  }

  const json = await res.json();

  if (json.error) {
    throw new Error(json.error);
  }

  return json;
}

import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest/wasm"
  );

  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath:
        "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@latest/models/pose_landmarker.task"
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE",
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  const raw = result.landmarks[0];

  // convert normalized  absolute canvas coords
  const joints = raw.map((kp) => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080,
  }));

  return joints;
}

Step 1 FINAL warpEngine.js

Place in:
src/utils/warpEngine.js

js
/**
 * Rigid limb rotation warp engine.
 * 
 * For each limb:
 *  - Create an offscreen canvas
 *  - Cut a simple rectangular region between joint A and joint B
 *  - Rotate this region around joint A (the pivot)
 *  - Return Konva-ready warped limb objects
 *
 * Output format:
 * {
 *   torso: HTMLImageElement,
 *   limbs: [
 *     {
 *       image: HTMLImageElement,
 *       x, y,
 *       rotation,
 *       pivotX, pivotY
 *     }
 *   ]
 * }
 */

export function computeLimbWarp(foreground, joints, basePose) {
  if (!foreground || !joints.length || !basePose) {
    return { torso: foreground, limbs: [] };
  }

  const limbs = [];

  // Helper to cut + rotate one limb rectangular region
  function createLimbRegion(aIdx, bIdx) {
    const a = joints[aIdx];
    const b = joints[bIdx];

    const baseA = basePose[aIdx];
    const baseB = basePose[bIdx];

    if (!a || !b || !baseA || !baseB) return null;

    // Limb vector
    const dx = b.x - a.x;
    const dy = b.y - a.y;
    const len = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

    // Base limb vector (for rotation difference)
    const bdx = baseB.x - baseA.x;
    const bdy = baseB.y - baseA.y;
    const baseLen = Math.sqrt(bdx * bdx + bdy * bdy);

    if (len < 2 || baseLen < 2) return null;

    // Angle difference from base pose
    const angleA = Math.atan2(dy, dx);
    const angleBase = Math.atan2(bdy, bdx);
    const angleDelta = (angleA - angleBase) * (180 / Math.PI);

    // Create bounding box for limb (simple rectangle)
    const thickness = 35; // fixed thickness for limb cut (MVP)
    const minX = a.x - thickness;
    const minY = a.y - thickness;
    const width = len + thickness * 2;
    const height = thickness * 2;

    // Create offscreen canvas
    const canvas = document.createElement("canvas");
    canvas.width = width;
    canvas.height = height;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

    // Draw from foreground
    ctx.drawImage(
      foreground,
      minX,
      minY,
      width,
      height,
      0,
      0,
      width,
      height
    );

    // Convert to image object for Konva
    const img = new Image();
    img.src = canvas.toDataURL("image/png");

    return {
      image: img,
      x: minX,
      y: minY,
      rotation: angleDelta,
      pivotX: a.x - minX,
      pivotY: a.y - minY,
    };
  }

  // Limb pairs for MVP
  const LIMB_PAIRS = [
    [11, 13], [13, 15], // left arm
    [12, 14], [14, 16], // right arm
    [23, 25], [25, 27], // left leg
    [24, 26], [26, 28], // right leg
  ];

  LIMB_PAIRS.forEach(([a, b]) => {
    const limb = createLimbRegion(a, b);
    if (limb) limbs.push(limb);
  });

  return { torso: foreground, limbs };
}

import { Stage, Layer, Rect, Image as KonvaImage, Circle, Line, Group } from "react-konva";
import { useEditor } from "../context/EditorContext";
import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";
import { computeLimbWarp } from "../utils/warpEngine";

// MediaPipe Pose connections for skeleton
const POSE_CONNECTIONS = [
  [11, 13], [13, 15],
  [12, 14], [14, 16],
  [11, 12],
  [12, 24], [11, 23],
  [23, 24],
  [23, 25], [25, 27],
  [27, 29], [29, 31],
  [24, 26], [26, 28],
  [28, 30], [30, 32],
];

const JOINT_RADIUS = 6;
const HIT_RADIUS = 16;

export default function CanvasStage({ showToast }) {
  const {
    foreground,
    joints,
    interpolatedJoints,
    imageOffset,
    interpolatedOffset,
    camera,
    interpolatedCamera,
    setJoints,
    setImageOffset,
    isPlaying,
    basePose
  } = useEditor();

  const activeJoints = isPlaying ? interpolatedJoints : joints;
  const activeOffset = isPlaying ? interpolatedOffset : imageOffset;
  const activeCamera = isPlaying ? interpolatedCamera : camera;

  const stageRef = useRef(null);
  const [scale, setScale] = useState(1);

  // Auto fit stage
  useEffect(() => {
    function updateScale() {
      const cw = window.innerWidth - 260;
      const ch = window.innerHeight - 180;
      setScale(Math.min(cw / 1920, ch / 1080, 1));
    }
    updateScale();
    window.addEventListener("resize", updateScale);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("resize", updateScale);
  }, []);

  // Center on segmentation
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!foreground) return;
    setImageOffset({ x: 1920 / 2 - 200, y: 1080 / 2 - 400 });
  }, [foreground]);

  // Dragging logic
  const [draggingIndex, setDraggingIndex] = useState(null);

  function getPointerPos() {
    const stage = stageRef.current;
    if (!stage) return { x: 0, y: 0 };
    const p = stage.getPointerPosition() || { x: 0, y: 0 };
    return { x: p.x / scale, y: p.y / scale };
  }

  function onMouseDown() {
    if (!activeJoints.length || isPlaying) return;
    const pos = getPointerPos();

    for (let i = 0; i < activeJoints.length; i++) {
      const j = activeJoints[i];
      const dx = pos.x - j.x;
      const dy = pos.y - j.y;
      if (Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) <= HIT_RADIUS) {
        setDraggingIndex(i);
        return;
      }
    }
  }

  function onMouseMove() {
    if (draggingIndex === null || isPlaying) return;

    const pos = getPointerPos();
    const updated = [...joints];

    const ROOT_L = 23;
    const ROOT_R = 24;

    if (draggingIndex === ROOT_L || draggingIndex === ROOT_R) {
      const dx = pos.x - updated[draggingIndex].x;
      const dy = pos.y - updated[draggingIndex].y;

      for (let i = 0; i < updated.length; i++) {
        updated[i] = { x: updated[i].x + dx, y: updated[i].y + dy };
      }

      setImageOffset({
        x: imageOffset.x + dx,
        y: imageOffset.y + dy
      });

      setJoints(updated);
      return;
    }

    updated[draggingIndex] = { x: pos.x, y: pos.y };
    setJoints(updated);
  }

  function onMouseUp() {
    setDraggingIndex(null);
  }

  // Camera transforms
  const cam = {
    scaleX: activeCamera.zoom,
    scaleY: activeCamera.zoom,

// MediaPipe pose connections
const POSE_CONNECTIONS = [
  [11, 13], [13, 15], // Left arm
  [12, 14], [14, 16], // Right arm
  [11, 12],           // Shoulders
  [12, 24], [11, 23], // Torso sides
  [23, 24],           // Hips
  [23, 25], [25, 27], // Left leg
  [27, 29], [29, 31], // Left shin/foot
  [24, 26], [26, 28], // Right leg
  [28, 30], [30, 32], // Right shin/foot
];

const JOINT_RADIUS = 6;
const HIT_RADIUS = 16;

export default function CanvasStage({ showToast }) {
  const {
    image,
    joints,
    interpolatedJoints,
    imageOffset,
    interpolatedOffset,
    camera,
    interpolatedCamera,
    foreground,
    setJoints,
    setImageOffset,
    isPlaying,
    basePose,
  } = useEditor();

  // Choose interpolated/live values depending on playback
  const activeJoints = isPlaying ? interpolatedJoints : joints;
  const activeOffset = isPlaying ? interpolatedOffset : imageOffset;
  const activeCamera = isPlaying ? interpolatedCamera : camera;

  const stageRef = useRef(null);
  const [scale, setScale] = useState(1);

  // ============================================
  // 1) AUTO SCALE DOWN, PRESERVE ASPECT RATIO
  // ============================================
  useEffect(() => {
    function updateScale() {
      const containerW = window.innerWidth - 260; // right panel reserved
      const containerH = window.innerHeight - 180; // toolbar + timeline

      const scaleX = containerW / 1920;
      const scaleY = containerH / 1080;
      const newScale = Math.min(scaleX, scaleY, 1);

      setScale(newScale);
    }

    updateScale();
    window.addEventListener("resize", updateScale);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("resize", updateScale);
  }, []);

      x: centerX - 200,

  // ============================================
  // 3) DRAGGING LOGIC
  // ============================================
  const [draggingIndex, setDraggingIndex] = useState(null);

  function getPointerPos() {
    const stage = stageRef.current;
    if (!stage) return { x: 0, y: 0 };

    const pointer = stage.getPointerPosition() || { x: 0, y: 0 };
    return {
      x: pointer.x / scale,
      y: pointer.y / scale,
    };
  }

  function onMouseDown() {
    if (!activeJoints.length || isPlaying) return;

    const pos = getPointerPos();

    for (let i = 0; i < activeJoints.length; i++) {
      const j = activeJoints[i];
      const dx = pos.x - j.x;
      const dy = pos.y - j.y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);

      if (dist <= HIT_RADIUS) {
        setDraggingIndex(i);
        return;
      }

UPDATED poseDetector.js (FINAL FIXED VERSION)

Replace your entire file with this:

js
import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm"
  );

  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath:
        "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm/pose_landmarker.task"
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE",
    numPoses: 1,
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  const raw = result.landmarks[0];

  return raw.map((kp) => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080,
  }));
}

Why this works

  • FilesetResolver loads WASM runtime from /wasm

  • Pose model .task files are stored in the same folder

  • 0.10.1 is the current stable release

  • URL now resolves correctly (no 404)

js
import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm"
  );

  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath:
        "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm/pose_landmarker_lite.task"
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE",
    numPoses: 1,
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  const raw = result.landmarks[0];

  return raw.map((kp) => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080,
  }));
}

js
import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm"
  );

  //  Use official Google-hosted model (NOT jsDelivr)
  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath:
        "https://storage.googleapis.com/mediapipe-assets/pose_landmarker_lite.task"
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE",
    numPoses: 1,
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  return result.landmarks[0].map(kp => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080,
  }));
}

js
import {
  PoseLandmarker,
  FilesetResolver
} from "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1";

let poseModel = null;

export async function loadPoseModel() {
  if (poseModel) return poseModel;

  const vision = await FilesetResolver.forVisionTasks(
    "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/tasks-vision@0.10.1/wasm"
  );

  poseModel = await PoseLandmarker.createFromOptions(vision, {
    baseOptions: {
      modelAssetPath: "/models/pose_landmarker_lite.task",   // LOCAL MODEL
    },
    runningMode: "IMAGE",
    numPoses: 1,
  });

  return poseModel;
}

export async function detectPose(imageBitmap) {
  if (!poseModel) await loadPoseModel();

  const result = poseModel.detect(imageBitmap);

  if (
    !result ||
    !result.landmarks ||
    !result.landmarks[0] ||
    result.landmarks[0].length !== 33
  ) {
    throw new Error("Pose detection failed or incomplete");
  }

  return result.landmarks[0].map(kp => ({
    x: kp.x * 1920,
    y: kp.y * 1080,
  }));
}
